<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-36-1113 </DOCNO><TEXT>A constant-current--driven semiconductor laser produced a field with amplitudenoise reduced to below the standard quantum limit by -1.7 dB (32%) overan entire frequency range from near dc to 1.1 GHz. The amplitude squeezingdependence on laser pump rate and optical loss was in good agreementwith theoretical prediction. The new squeezed-state generation principleof high impedance suppression for pump-amplitude fluctuation was thusconfirmed experimentally.</TEXT></DOC>